tourBios.carHigh:
2014: Finished T64 at the Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament in December. Was tie for 11th after 54 holes but closed 72-74-72.

2011: Monday qualifier at the PGA TOUR's Wyndham Championship, where he posted scores of 75-72 and missed the cut.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Former No. 1-ranked junior golfer in Zimbabwe...Named Towson University's 2010 Athlete of the Year, only the third golfer in school history to receive the honor...Had a win and five top-10 finishes his junior and senior years with the Tigers...Helped his team to the Colonial Athletic Association championship in 2010. Tied for first at the Joe Agee Invitational in Williamsburg, Va., his senior year.
tourBios.personal: Both of his parents are doctors and the family moved to the United States in 2005...Speaks Shona, a Bantu language native to the Shona people of Zimbabwe and Southern Zambia...Says if he weren't a professional golfer he'd be a financial analyst...Twitter name is @nyashamauchaza...Favorite course he's played is Wingate Park GC in Zimbabwe and would like to play at St. Andrews and Augusta National...Marks his ball on the greens with pennies...Favorite teams are Manchester United and the Philadelphia Eagles...Favorite movies are "My Cousin Vinny" and those starring Denzel Washington...Would include Dave Chappelle, Richard Pryor and Jimmy Fallon in his dream foursome...Would like to trade places for a day with theoretical physicist Edward Witten to get his perspective on things...Bucket list includes playing golf at Crans-sur-Sierre, a Jack Nicklaus signature course in Switzerland. Would also like to experience zero gravity and compete in the Olympics.
